        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): clear daily-ingestion sqlite namespace on dreaming repair",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: `repairDreamingArtifacts()` (driven by `openclaw memory status --fix`) archives the dreaming session corpus and clears the migrated SQLite ingestion state, but it only clears the `dreaming-session-ingestion-files` and `dreaming-session-ingestion-seen` namespaces. It never clears the migrated `dreaming-daily-ingestion` namespace.\n- **Why it matters**: This is the repair-side counterpart of the audit change merged in #92020 (fixes #92017). That PR taught `auditDreamingArtifacts()` to treat **all three** ingestion namespaces — including `dreaming-daily-ingestion` — as \"ingestion state present\" after the legacy JSON sidecars were migrated to SQLite. The repair path was not updated to match, so:\n  1. After a repair, the `memory status --fix` flow immediately re-audits and still reports `sessionIngestionExists: true` solely because the daily-ingestion rows survive — a self-contradicting phantom state right after a \"successful\" repair.\n  2. The daily-ingestion bookkeeping (which daily memory files were already ingested) leaks past the repair, so the daily files are not re-ingested on the next sweep. This breaks the repair's intent of resetting dreaming ingestion to a clean rebuildable state.\n- The legacy sidecars are siblings by design: `dreaming-phases.ts` lists `daily-ingestion.json` and `session-ingestion.json` side by side as the legacy ingestion JSON files, and issue #92017 archives both together.\n\n## What changed\n\n- `extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-repair.ts` — `clearSessionIngestionState()` now also clears `DREAMING_DAILY_INGESTION_NAMESPACE`, alongside the existing session files/seen namespaces. (The constant was already imported by #92020.) Added a comment documenting that all three ingestion namespaces must be cleared together to stay symmetric with the audit.\n- `extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-repair.test.ts` — two regression tests:\n  - `clears sqlite daily ingestion state when archiving session corpus` — asserts the daily namespace is emptied after repair.\n  - `re-audit reports ingestion absent after repairing daily-only ingestion state` — reproduces the CLI `--fix` audit → repair → re-audit flow and asserts the re-audit no longer reports a phantom ingestion state.\n\nNo change to the dreaming pipeline, the migration, or the CLI output formatting.\n\n## Real behavior proof (real runtime, outside tests)\n\nA `tsx` script drove the real exported `auditDreamingArtifacts` / `repairDreamingArtifacts` against a **real on-disk SQLite state DB** (`OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR` pointed at a temp dir; `node:sqlite` is the real backend). The daily-ingestion rows are read back through an **independent read-only `node:sqlite` handle opened directly on the `openclaw.sqlite` file** — i.e. the assertion crosses the real disk boundary, not an in-process return value.\n\n**Command**: `TSX_TSCONFIG_PATH=tsconfig.json node --import tsx proof-daily-clear.mts`\n\n**Output (after fix)**:\n```text\n  state db path = /tmp/proof-state-N4F9Vr/state/openclaw.sqlite\n== STEP 1: daily rows on disk BEFORE repair ==\n  plugin_state_entries[memory-core/dreaming-daily-ingestion] = 1\n== STEP 2: real auditDreamingArtifacts BEFORE repair ==\n  sessionIngestionExists = true\n== STEP 3: real repairDreamingArtifacts (archives corpus + clears SQLite) ==\n  archivedSessionCorpus = true\n  warnings = []\n== STEP 4: daily rows on disk AFTER repair (independent sqlite handle) ==\n  plugin_state_entries[memory-core/dreaming-daily-ingestion] = 0\n== STEP 5: real auditDreamingArtifacts AFTER repair (CLI --fix re-audit) ==\n  sessionIngestionExists = false\n== RESULT ==\nPASS: daily-ingestion namespace cleared from disk; re-audit no longer reports phantom ingestion state\n```\n\n**Negative control (fix reverted — daily clear removed)**, same script:\n```text\n== STEP 4: daily rows on disk AFTER repair (independent sqlite handle) ==\n  plugin_state_entries[memory-core/dreaming-daily-ingestion] = 1\n== STEP 5: real auditDreamingArtifacts AFTER repair (CLI --fix re-audit) ==\n  sessionIngestionExists = true\n== RESULT ==\nFAIL: daily-ingestion namespace not fully cleared / audit still reports ingestion present\n```\n\nThe daily rows survive the repair and the re-audit reports a phantom `true` without the fix — confirming the symmetric gap.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-repair.test.ts` → 9 passed (7 existing + 2 new).\n- Negative control: with the daily-clear reverted, exactly the 2 new tests fail (`expected true to be false` on the re-audit), the other 7 pass — the tests pin the bug.\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs` → clean.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- **Blast radius**: One private helper in `dreaming-repair.ts`; only adds a clear of an already-imported namespace. No public API/signature change.\n- **Behavioral risk**: Repair already clears the two sibling ingestion namespaces and archives the daily-ingestion JSON sidecar on the filesystem side; clearing the SQLite daily namespace makes the SQLite path consistent with both. Clearing is idempotent and wrapped in the existing try/catch that records a warning on failure.\n- **Backward compatibility**: Repair only runs under explicit `--fix`; an empty daily-ingestion namespace simply causes daily memory files to be re-ingested on the next sweep, which is the intended post-repair behavior.\n",
        "branch": "fix/dreaming-repair-clear-daily-ingestion",
